00:31:33.850 --> 00:31:38.630
that we can take a blood sample
or a cell from a urine specimen

00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:42.420
and we can, from that,
deconvolute the cell so

00:31:42.420 --> 00:31:46.290
that it does not know what was
the tissue it was derived from.

00:31:46.290 --> 00:31:49.740
And then we can alter
its genetic information

00:31:49.740 --> 00:31:52.700
and grow it back into
a heart cell, which

00:31:52.700 --> 00:31:55.610
is really important, because
we have no heart cell lines--

00:31:55.610 --> 00:31:58.990
none-- in any species,
including human.

00:31:58.990 --> 00:32:02.030
And we can, for the first
time, study these in a dish.

00:32:02.030 --> 00:32:05.310
This provides an opportunity
that we simply could not

00:32:05.310 --> 00:32:09.450
do without combining both lots
of advanced cell therapies

00:32:09.450 --> 00:32:11.080
with the capacity to editing.

00:32:11.080 --> 00:32:13.040
So when you hear that
the world is just

00:32:13.040 --> 00:32:17.211
beginning to use this
technology, Jacob's 100% right.

